title: Import & Processing
text: spiro package supports different metabolic carts. metabolic cart data file produced usually determined automatically, can also set manually spiro() function. Currently package supports following devices: CORTEX ("cortex"): .xlsx, .xls .xml files German language COSMED ("cosmed"): .xlsx .xls files English German language VYNTUS ("vyntus"): .txt files (tab-seperated) German language ZAN ("zan"): .dat files, usually name "EXED*" German language highly recommended import raw breath--breath data analyze available data avoid duplication interpolation processes. import data without processing (interpolation) use function spiro_import(): Alternatively can access raw data spiro() call extracting "raw" attribute result.

title: Summarizing & Plotting
text: types exercise tests may preferable get maximal values measured parameters. spiro_max() calculates smoothing data. smooth argument controls interval method data smoothing. Smoothing happens calculation rolling average either fixed time interval (e.g. smooth = 30 30 seconds), fixed number breaths (e.g. smooth = "30b" 30 breaths). Per default smoothing apply heart rate values, can enable behavior hr_smooth = TRUE.
code: spiro_max(gxt_data, smooth = 30) #>       VO2    VCO2 VO2_rel     VE  RER HR #> 1 4732.28 4640.75    71.7 129.62 1.14 NA

title: Summarizing & Plotting
text: spiro package lets visualize data cardiopulmonary exercise testing: spiro_plot() can display traditional Wasserman 9-Panel Plot.  can individually select combine panels 9-Panel Plot setting argument.  Data time (Panel 1,2,3,6,8,9) displayed smoothing average interval set smooth argument. panels (4,5,7) use initial raw data visualization. can control appearance plots spiro_plot(). Use base_size argument change plot base size. Pass style arguments ggplot::theme() customization.
code: # load example data data <- spiro(spiro_example("zan_ramp"),                        hr_file = spiro_example("hr_ramp.tcx"))  spiro_plot(data) # Plot only V-Slope (Panel 5) and VO2/VCO2 over time (Panel 3) spiro_plot(data, which = c(5,3)) # Change base size and  spiro_plot(data, base_size = 9, axis.title = ggplot2::element_text(face = "italic", colour = "blue"))
